<p class="guide-intro">Thoughtful questions that show preparation, curiosity, and strong role fit judgment.</p>

<section class="guide-section">
  <h2>Recruiter / Intro Screen</h2>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>What does success look like in the first 90 days for this role?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Signals ownership mindset and helps you calibrate ramp expectations.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>How has this role evolved in the last 12 months?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Reveals whether scope is growing strategically or reacting to churn.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>What are the top reasons candidates decline offers here?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Surfaces potential fit risks early and invites transparent discussion.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="guide-section">
  <h2>Hiring Manager</h2>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>What are the biggest team priorities this quarter, and where would this role contribute first?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Connects your potential impact to real, current business priorities.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>How do you balance delivery speed with quality and technical debt?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Exposes decision culture and engineering standards in practice.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>What’s a recent decision your team changed course on, and why?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Shows how the team learns, adapts, and handles uncertainty.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="guide-section">
  <h2>Panel / Cross-Functional</h2>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>Where do cross-team handoffs usually break down, and what improves them?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Identifies collaboration friction and your ability to navigate it.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>How are product, engineering, and design tradeoffs resolved when priorities conflict?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Reveals decision rights and partnership maturity.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>What behaviors make someone especially effective on this team?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Gives concrete culture signals beyond generic values statements.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="guide-section">
  <h2>Final Round / Close</h2>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>What concerns, if any, do you still have about my fit?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Creates space to address objections directly and demonstrates confidence.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>If I joined, what would make you say in six months that this was a great hire?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Clarifies practical performance expectations and stakeholder priorities.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="guide-item">
    <h3>What are the next major inflection points for the company and this team?</h3>
    <p><strong>Why this is strong:</strong> Helps you evaluate growth trajectory and timing risk.</p>
  </article>
</section>
